<hr>
<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
In parentheses, name the original authors, followed by &#8216;qtd. in&#8217;, and then the author(s) and relevant page numbers from the secondary work you read. For example, material by Jones and Chan was quoted in a work by Smith, but you did not read the work by Jones and Chan.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (Jones and Chan qtd. in Smith 25&#45;26).
</blockquote>
<br>
Or include the original authors in your sentence, with the secondary author and relevant page 
number(s) in parentheses.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Jones and Chan suggested that &#34;the default position is markedly affected&#34; 
	(qtd. in Smith 23).
</blockquote>
